Okay... I have been looking for a version of this which doesn't set my A/V alarms off... they all seem the same.

Ultimate solution is.... UnUPX the KG and the alarms stop going off. XD

In order to do that (with Avast) I had to disable the run-time shield, extract the keygen.exe, pass it through UPX to uncompress (I used CFF Explorer, but UniExtractor or UPX will work just as well) and then enable the run-time shield.

To confirm, I performed a deep scan on the uncompressed exe, and it's fine... there are no threats in it aside from the compression. :D
